## New for this step: fixing real Ruby bugs in flight

Four issues found and fixed while planning this step (all local-only or
Ruby-source changes, all confirmed via direct reproduction before fixing):

1. **`BOUKENSHA_DIR` off-by-one** in `examples/example.rb` (3 `../` instead
   of 4) — the same bug every prior step has shipped with first. 5th
   occurrence across 4 steps. Fixed the same way.
2. **`Context#register_tool` had regressed** to the unfixed
   `@tools[tool.name] = tool` (missing the `02_the_registry`
   string-normalization fix — this file's copy predates that fix). Reapplied
   the same fix, same reasoning as `02_the_registry`'s.
3. **`PromptBuilder#to_messages` had an arity bug that broke 3 of 5
   backends.** It called `@backend.to_messages(@context.messages)` (1 arg)
   uniformly, but Anthropic/Gemini's `to_messages(messages)` takes 1 arg
   while Ollama/OllamaCloud/OpenAI's `to_messages(system, messages)` takes 2
   (they embed the system prompt inline in the messages array; Anthropic/
   Gemini send it as a separate top-level payload field instead). Confirmed
   reproducible: `builder.to_messages` raised `ArgumentError: wrong number
   of arguments (given 1, expected 2)` for Ollama/OllamaCloud/OpenAI, while
   `to_api_payload` worked fine everywhere (each backend's own `to_payload`
   already called its `to_messages` with the right arity internally).
   **Fixed by user decision (2026-07-22)**: standardized all five backends
   on `to_messages(system, messages)`. Anthropic/Gemini now accept (and
   ignore) `system`, so `PromptBuilder#to_messages` can delegate uniformly
   without special-casing which backends need it inline.
4. **`.boukensha/settings.yaml`'s `model: claude-sonnet-5` isn't in
   `Anthropic::MODELS`** (only `claude-haiku-4-5(-20251001)`,
   `claude-sonnet-4-6`, `claude-opus-4-8` were listed) — running the example
   against the real shared settings file raised `UnsupportedModelError`,
   which would have blocked this step's byte-for-byte parity test entirely.
   **Fixed by user decision (2026-07-22)**: added a `claude-sonnet-5` entry
   to `Anthropic::MODELS` (same `context_window`/`cost_per_million` tier as
   `claude-sonnet-4-6`, since it's the real current Sonnet model). Mirror
   this entry in the Python port's `Anthropic` backend too.

Additionally, running `examples/example.rb` needs `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` set
(`ENV.fetch`) even though no live API call is ever made — `PromptBuilder`
only builds the payload (see README: "PromptBuilder does not call the API").
Added a local-only `.boukensha/.env` with a dummy value for this
(`.boukensha/*` is gitignored except `.keep`, so this never reaches git).
If a real key is preferred there instead, that's a drop-in replacement of
the same line — nothing about the port depends on which one is present.

None of the four issues above are things the Ruby source itself frames as
an open question (unlike the still-open `register_tool` public-API
duplication question from `02_the_registry`, left alone as before) — these
are straightforward reproducible bugs or a config/model-table mismatch, in
scope for the "fix real bugs found in flight" authorization.

