### `examples/example.rb` → `examples/example.py`

Port 1:1: register `look` (no params) and `move` tools through the
registry, add the same 3 messages (user/assistant/tool_result), resolve
`provider`/`model` from `config.tasks("player")`, branch on provider to
construct the right backend (mirroring the Ruby `case`/`when` with an
`if`/`elif` chain — raising `ValueError` for an unsupported provider,
matching Ruby's `ArgumentError`), build a `PromptBuilder`, and
`json.dumps(builder.to_api_payload(), indent=2)` in place of
`JSON.pretty_generate`. Verify the two pretty-printers produce identical
formatting (indent width, key order) before trusting a byte-diff — Python
dicts preserve insertion order same as Ruby hashes, so key order should
already match as long as each payload dict is built in the same order as
Ruby's.

